@77   = ~Amulets are usually magical devices that are commonly worn around the neck, suspended from a chain.  The type of chain that comes with an amulet generally increases the item's aesthetic value, not its magical properties. Only one amulet can be dangled from the neck at a time.  ~
@78   = ~The Necromancers Rage
  Before the Time of Troubles, a powerful Thayan Red Wizard spent many years specializing and studying the art of Necromancy. Finally he made his bid for power within Thay and many wizards fell before his skill. However, as he neared his goal of domination of Thay, he was challenged by a powerful illusionist. They battled for nearly a hour. The illusionist wove many deceiving spells about himself. The necromancer had no knowledge of illusion, and so could not pierce them. He was forced to concede. As he left he cursed necromancy and vowed never to use it again. The final spell he cast was to create this amulet that destroyed necromantic magic - his final revenge on that spell school.

  STATISTICS
  
  Abilities: +5 Bonus to all saves vs. death
  Wearer immune to all necromantic magic~
@79   = ~Silver Amulet~
@80   = ~Cowled Wizard Badge~
@81   = ~This badge signifies you as an honorary member of the Cowled Wizards. It is carried by the most important cowled wizards to protect them from the magically insane. The badge grants many protections and allows the wearer to cast Contingency and Minor Spell Sequencer once every day.

  STATISTICS
  While Equipped:
  1 extra wizard spell at 1st, 2nd and 3rd level.
   Vocalize
   Immunity to Level Drain~
@82   = ~Ring~
@83   = ~Red Wizard Ring~
@84   = ~A ring is a small band of precious metal that is used as jewelry.  Some rare rings have had enchantments placed upon them that confer various magical abilities.  These rings are highly sought after, especially by those of the adventuring profession.~
@85   = ~This is a ring made by the Red Wizards of Thay. It is given to wizards performing a task of supposed national importance. It is very rare to find this ring in the possession of anyone but a Red Wizard.
  STATISTICS:
  Grants 50%  fire resistance
  Increases spell casting speed by 2~
@86   = ~Artifact~
@87   = ~The Artifact sits ominously in your hand. Its black, warped surface seems to throb slightly with barely-contained energy. It is plain to see that this object contains vast magical power.~
@88   = ~<No Text>~
@89   = ~Black Blade of Disaster~
@90   = ~Two-Handed Sword~
@91   = ~Pains Shard +6~
@92   = ~The two-handed sword is a derivative of the long sword.  Weaponsmiths have always looked for ways to improve existing weapons.  In an effort to improve the long sword, the blade was lengthened.  Eventually, the handle had to be extended and two hands became necessary to properly swing the sword.  The primary function of two-handed swords is cleaving mounted knights and breaking up pike formations. 
  
  STATISTICS:
  
  Damage:  1D10
  Damage type:  slashing
  Weight: 15
  Speed Factor: 10
  Proficiency Type: Two Handed sword
  Type:  2-handed
  Requires: 14 Strength~
@93   = ~Pain's Shard +6
  This blade sparkles with magical energy as you draw it through the air. It seems to almost cut through the Planes themselves, leaving a blackness in its wake. This blade once adorned the Lady of Pain, the powerful ruler of Sigil, but was given to you by her for your great service. It protects from many things, including cold and instant death, as well as granting magic resistance and regeneration. When it strikes a target, there is a good chance that the target will be wracked with incredible pain. The blade also anchors the wielder to their plane of existence, making them immune to Maze and Imprisonment spells.
  So sharp is the blade that it cuts through reality itself. With each hit there is a small chance that the target will be thrown into another plane of existence. The sharpness of the blade also allows the wielder to cut through any magic that might hinder movement. Finally, the blade contains some of the power of the Lady. The wielder may access this power, allowing them to use the blade to cut through space and teleport to their desired location at will. It also allows them to cast the Banishment spell once a day, that flings one target into oblivion.  The blade cuts through magic as well and so with each hit the target may lose magic resistance or have physical spell protections removed.

  EQUIPPED EFFECTS:
  While equipped, this blade protects the wielder from all forms of instant death magic (disintegration and petrification)
  +25% Magic Resistance 
  Immune to Imprisonment and Maze spells
  +2 to Armour Class

  STATISTICS
  Combat Abilities: With each hit there 50% chance that the target receives cumulative 1 point penalty to their THAC0 - Duration: 20 rounds
  With each hit the target loses 5% magic resistance - Duration: 50 rounds
  With each hit the target must make a save versus spells at -3 or be affected by terrible pain. The pain reduces their dexterity by 2 and lowers their saving throws by 2 - Duration: 20 rounds
  With each hit there is a 10% chance that the target will be imprisoned in a outer planar reality, but is allowed a save versus death at +4
  THAC0: +6 bonus
  Damage: 1D8 +6
  Damage type:  slashing
  Weight:  10
  Speed Factor: 6
  Proficiency Type: Two handed sword
  Type:  2-handed
  Requires: 14 Strength~
@94   = ~Ring of Free Action:  'Edventar's Gift'
  This ring was given to the reef scavenger and hunter, known only as Edventar, by a group of aquatic elves who had long been his friends. His help in routing the "Pirate Queen", Yenandra of Dambrath, was instrumental in their survival, though Yenandra continues to be feared anywhere the water meets land.
  
  STATISTICS:
  
  Special:  The wearer is immune to everything, magical and otherwise, that affects mobility in any way. This includes haste and slow spells.~
@95   = ~Quarterstaff~
@96   = ~Staff of Sorcery~
@97   = ~The simplest and humblest of staff weapons, the quarterstaff is a length of wood ranging six to nine feet in length.  High quality quarterstaves are made of stout oak and are shod with metal at both ends.  The quarterstaff must be wielded with both hands.  
  
  STATISTICS:
  
  Damage:  1D6
  Damage type:  crushing
  Weight: 4
  Speed Factor: 4
  Proficiency Type: Staff
  Type:  2-handed
  Requires: 5 Strength~
@98   = ~Staff of Sorcery +5
  Most Staff of the Magi share powers in common. The more powerful staves, like the one famously owned by Khelben "Blackstaff" Arunsun are rare, and the property of powerful Archwizards. This staff however outdoes them all. Its twisted black surface seems to shine with no light, and yet at the same time all the colors of the rainbow. It is not composed of  any material you can name, but feels as if it is woven of solid mists. This staff is believed to have been created by the ArchSorcerer Melanthium, the most powerful being to have ever existed and notorious enemy of the Lady of Pain. He carried the staff merely because he felt that it was part of the image, so he only enchanted it with his lesser magics. Like the sorcerer himself, this staff is incredibly powerful. It increases the user's ability to cast spells, protects the user from lesser weapons and spells cast at the user, and allows the casting of powerful spells with a wave of the staff.
STATISTICS
  Armour Class: +4 bonus
  Saving Throws: +4 bonus

Equipped Abilities:
  Protection from Petrification
  Protection From Instant Death
  Protection From Imprisonment
  Protection From 1st to 3rd level spells.
  Protection from Fear
  Immunity to Normal and +1 Weapons.
  Immunity to Level Drain
  +15 Hit Points
  Grants the user the ability to memorize one extra spell per level
  
  Abilities:
  Five times a day the staff can unleash magical fireballs.
  Once a day the power of the staff can be used to protect the user from all magic for half a minute. 
  Improved Disintegration can be cast thrice a day. 
  The staff can cast the Chain Contingency spell.
  Combat Ability (each hit): Dispel Magic  
  Will slay any extra planar creature with less then 4d10 hit points - they are allowed a save at -4.
  THAC0: +5 bonus  
  Damage:  1D6 +5
  Damage type:  crushing
  Weight: 4
  Speed Factor: 4
  Proficiency Type: Quarterstaff
  Type:  2-handed
  Requires: 5 Strength~
@99   = ~Dispel Effects~
@100  = ~Circlet of Infernal Shielding~
@101  = ~Circlet of Infernal Shielding
  This magical circlet feels hot to the touch and, as you place it on your finger, it flares with magic and a ring of fire springs up around you. This ring is believed to have been created many years ago by a mage studying fire elementals. Unfortunately, the protection provided by this ring grants did not save him when a stupid student released his fiery captives.
  STATISTICS:
  
  Equipped Abilities:  
  30% Cold Resistance
  User affected with the Fire Shield (Red) spell.
  ~
@102  = ~Wand ~
@103  = ~Stave of Jagged Lightning ~
@104  = ~Wands are 1 1/4 feet long and slender.  They are made of ivory, bone, or wood and are usually tipped with something - metal, crystal, stone, etc.  They are fragile and tend to break easily. Because of this, they are often kept in cases.  
  
  Wands are powered by charges, each use costing one or more charges (depending on the item).  When a wand runs out of charges, it is consumed and destroyed.~
@105  = ~Stave of Jagged Lightning 
  The origin of this particular type of stave is unknown. Several exist, but so few that they are highly valued. This Stave was rediscovered recently when a group of pirates hijacked the floating ship of a Halruuan mage in Waterdeep. This was one of the items they "recovered", though what became of the mage is unknown. Originally possessing many charges, the stave has been used many times, and so many have been used. There are few left.

  STATISTICS:
  
  Effect: Chain Lightning
  Damage:  4D6 (save vs. wands for half)
  Range:  100ft
  
  Effect: Call Lightning
  Damage:  8D8 (save vs. wands for half)
  Range:  110ft~
@106  = ~Staff of the Battle Magi +4~
@107  = ~Staff of the Battle Magi +4
  Trelecar, a powerful fighter of Tethyr, discovered his magical ability half way through his adventuring career. After several years of training, he became a relatively powerful mage. However, he could not help but remember his fighting abilities, so he crafted this powerful staff that allowed him to use both his brawling talent and spellcasting skills.
  The staff protects its holder in combat, and gives them increased strength and constitution, as well as giving them various other magical abilities. The staff's magic makes it do more damage then a staff would normally do.
  
  STATISTICS:
  +2 Strength and Constitution.
  -3 Base Armour Class
  +10% Resistance to all forms of physical attack.
  +5 Hit Points
  Can cast Tenser's Transformation and Protection from Normal Missiles once a day.  
  THACO: +4
  Damage: 2D6 + 4
  Damage Type: Crushing
  Weight: 4
  Speed Factor: 1
  Proficiency Type: Quarterstaff
  Type:  2-handed
  Requires: 5 Strength~
@108  = ~Amulet~
@109  = ~Amulet of Advancing~
@110  = ~Amulet of Advancing
  Created with the blood of an Elder Orb, this item increases the mage's ability to memorize spells at a high level. Its creator, while an able forger of magical items, was too humane for his own good, and chose to steal the blood from the Elder Orb rather then kill it. The Elder Orb was slightly less caring about his "Live and Let Live" attitude. The teeth marks can still be seen on this amulet. 

  STATISTICS:
  Special:  Memorize one extra seventh level spell~
@111  = ~Rod of Avarda Kedarva~
@112  = ~Wands are 1 1/4 feet long and slender.  They are made of ivory, bone, or wood and are usually tipped with something - metal, crystal, stone, etc.  They are fragile and tend to break easily.  Because of this, they are often kept in cases.  
  
  Wands are powered by charges, each use costing one or more charges (depending on the item).  When a wand runs out of charges, it is consumed and destroyed.~
@113  = ~Rod of Avarda Kedarva
  Avarda Kedarva was a powerful Necromancer of Ancient Netheril. A vile Archmage, he wanted to destroy the magical city in which he resided. What he planned to do was unknown. However, the Rod came into his plan. The Rod is a powerful and terrible thing, originally gifted with many charges, but over time it has been used well, generally by the most evil characters in the Realms. It is now covered in burns, cracks and scars, but retains some of its original power. 
  The Rod unleashes a powerful blast of magical energy that consumes the target in a blinding flash of green light. The target, if it cannot resist the magic, is instantly killed.
 
  STATISTICS:
  Effects: Kills target instantly unless save vs. death at -3
  Range: 100
  Area: 1 creature
  Duration: Permanent~
@114  = ~Bolt~
@115  = ~Doom Bolt +3~
@116  = ~Quarrels or bolts are the ammunition fired by crossbows regardless of the weapon's size.
  
  STATISTICS:
  
  Damage:  1D8
  Damage type:  missile (piercing)
  Weight:  0
  Launcher:  Crossbow~
@117  = ~This bolt makes you feel very uneasy as you hold it, filling you with a sense of almost impending doom. Around a thousand of these magical bolts were originally created to guard the High Temple of Bane. After the Time of Troubles, they spread throughout the Realms. They have been enchanted to hit more often and do more damage. 
  
  STATISTICS:
  Damage: 1D8+3
  THAC0: +3
  Damage type: Missile (Piercing)
  Special: Save vs. spell or be affected with Doom spell. 
  Duration: Permanent
  Weight: 0
  Launcher: Crossbow~
@118  = ~Doomed~
@119  = ~Gloves~
@120  = ~Gloves of Spell Weaving~
@121  = ~These gloves are woven of absolute night and radiate power.~
@122  = ~Gloves of Spell Weaving
  These gloves crackle with magical energy. They are made of fine black material that seems to be woven from the void itself. These gloves were created by the Archsorcerer Melanthium, and seem to literally draw magic to them. When donned, the user's magical abilities are greatly increased. The speed of spell casting and its duration are affected, and the user's ability to cast spells is greatly improved. Oddly enough, they seem never to have been worn. Probably because it is unlikely that the Archsorcerer ever needed them. It also allows the user to drain power from a opponent or destroy magical barriers with a single wave of the user's hand.
  
  STATISTICS
  Special Abilities: 
  Spell-casting speed is increased and the spell speed factor is increased.
  Also, the wearer is able to memorize 1 extra spell per level. 
  They also increase the user's Intelligence and Wisdom by 1 point.
  Cast Energy Drain and spell strike once a day.~
@123  = ~Hourglass~
@124  = ~Sands of Time~
@125  = ~This small hourglass contains sparkling blue sands that continually flow from one bulb to the other. Strangely enough, the level of sand in each bulb never seems to change. If you stare hard enough, you can just see strange runes engraved on the side.~
@126  = ~Sands of Time
  Aoskar, the God of Portals that the Lady of Pain deposed from power, was placed in charge of the passage of time of many planes. When he and the Lady fought for power, it is believed the power with which he controlled time was shattered. As he fell, these the Sands of Time rained across Sigil. A resourceful Archmage in Sigil collected some of the sands, imprisoning them inside this hourglass. The sand in this hourglass appears to continually flow, no matter how much the hourglass is tilted or shaken. However, engraved on the side of the hour glass is a Word of Power that, when spoken, causes the sands to halt their passage, and stop the flow of time around the caster for a short time. 
   
  STATISTICS:  
  Special Abilities (once per day): Stop the passage of time
  ~
@127  = ~Scroll~
@128  = ~Scroll of Kaza~
@129  = ~This scroll radiates energy, but of an evil nature. Caution is recommended.~
@130  = ~This scroll is covered in strange twisted writings. It appears to be a translation from the Book of Kaza, which details in full how an advanced mage could transform themselves into a Lich, a powerful undead spellcaster. This spell scroll is strange in that, unlike other lich transformations, no long ritual is required, and the caster's dead form becomes the soul container. Beware, however! While the transformation into a Lich brings many benefits, it also has terrible consequences. Immortality takes a long time to get right.

  Abilities:
  User is transformed into a Lich, and gains the following abilities.
  -2 to Dexterity
  -4 to Charisma
  +1 to Strength, Constitution and Intelligence 
  Spell casting speed increased by one.
  +10 Hit Points
  One extra 1st-4th level spell
  Fire does extra damage
  +2 bonus to Saves vs Death and Spells.
  Immunity to Cold
  Immunity to Level Drain
  Immunity to Instant Death 
  Immunity to Poison
  Immunity to Non-Magical Weapons
  Immunity to Sleep
  Immunity to Polymorph
  +50% Piercing Resistance
  +10% Resistance to all other forms of attack. 
  +5%  Magic Resistance 
  Alignment set to Neutral Evil
  Infravision 
  Party will loose 8 Reputation
  Gains ability to Control Undead thrice a day. Also gains the ability to Lich Touch thrice a day, and the new Lich gets an Aura of Fear, so that any creature close enough to attack the character must make a Save vs Spells or run in fear.
  Caster must be above 18th level, or the results could be disastrous. Be warned that healing spells will no longer affect the Lich. As such, the Lich must rely on their innate regeneration to protect themselves.~
@131  = ~Large Shield~
@132  = ~Rift Shield +5~
@133  = ~This shield is a dull black, and appears completely inactive.  However, as you gaze at the surface for an instant, you think you catch a brief glance of a swirling mass of magical energy that seems somehow malevolent.  ~
@134  = ~Rift Shield +5
  As you gaze at the face of this dull black shield, its enchantment is not immediately apparent. However, as you touch it, a strange cold runs up your arm, and the face of the shield seems to distort and change. The shield face, when the shield is touched, becomes a twisting black portal to some other dimension. Objects may pass freely through the portal and are completely irretrievable, no doubt ending up floating in another plane of existence. Attacks made against the holder are severely hindered by the magical gate, and all missiles hitting the shield are absorbed into the rift. The shield however is strangely unnerving to anyone looking at its face, as an observer gets the distinct impression that something beyond the rift is staring back. 
 
  STATISTICS:
  Immunity to Missile Weapons
  +10% Magic Resistance
  -2 Charisma
  +6 Armour Class
  Weight: 3
  Requires: 5 Strength~
@135  = ~Shattered Tale +4~
@136  = ~Two Handed Sword +4 - Shattered Tale
  Though not originally magical, certain events led to the enchantment of this blade. It is known by the wisest sages that certain themes run throughout the history of all realities, and that they are engraved in the very substance of creation. One of the best know themes is the noble prince rescuing the beautiful princess from the wicked witch. In this case however something went horribly wrong. The prince had battled his way through hordes of undead and through the mandatory Field of Thorns. He faced the witch in single combat, slaying the foul creature with a stroke of this sword. He climbed the tower and entered the princess' chamber. In a fit of passion, they ran towards each other their arms outstretched... The prince tripped, knocking the princess through the open window onto the mangled thorns below. His sword came loose as he fell, skewering him through the chest and killing him instantly. The normal theme of things had been broken, and the power of the story shattered. Some of it passing into this blade, causing it to become a powerful weapon. The shard of story residing in the blade makes it the typical and somewhat clichéd weapon of happiness ever after.

  STATISTICS:
  +1 Charisma and Constitution.
  User immune to particularly evil spells like Unholy Word, Doom and Unholy Blight
  +5% Magic Resistance
  However, the fact the story went wrong also resides in the blade, and gives -2 to Wisdom.
  THAC0: +4 bonus, +6 vs Evil
  Damage:  1D12 +4, +6 vs Evil
  Damage type:  slashing
  Weight:  11
  Speed Factor: 6
  Proficiency Type: Two handed sword 
  Type:  2-handed
  Requires: 14 Strength~
@137  = ~Gem~
@138  = ~Primus Gem~
@139  = ~Within this gem floats a strange mist. As you gaze into it, numbers and symbols seem to float past your eyes, giving you a minor headache.~
@140  = ~Primus Gem
  This gem comes from the center of a Modron's body. The Modrons are strange mechanical beings who reside on the plane of Mechanus. These gems are found in the power center of the Modron's body, and are their link with the Plane of Mechanus. Hence it is rare to find one intact, as they are usually destroyed when the Modron is killed. By smashing the gem, the energy within can be released and absorbed, giving the user the benefit of a Modron's intelligence.

  STATISTICS:
  Intelligence:  Raised by 1 point permanently
  Special:  The gem shatters upon use.
  Usage:  Place into quick item slot~
@141  = ~Intelligence has been raised by 1 permanently~
@142  = ~Ioun Stone~
@143  = ~Shadowy Black Ioun Stone~
@144  = ~This is a small stone that floats in an orbit around the owner's head. Simply equip the stone to set it in its orbit. These obviously magical stones have different properties depending on their color.~
@145  = ~Shadowy Black Ioun Stone:
  It is believed that only around four of these ioun stones are still in existence. They have been banned by all magical organizations throughout Faerún because they promote extreme unrest among the magical community. These gems are easy to make, and cheap as well. However, the dispute arises from one of their creation components... the power of a mage. Unfortunately, a mage has to be killed in the creation of these items and so, as you might imagine, murders and assassinations were carried out right and left, until the magical community in general banned the construction of these stones, and destroyed all the stones they could find. Anyone found with this stone by a magical organization is likely to be heavily penalized. The stone's power deserves its reputation however, making its users magical abilities much stronger.  
  
  Abilities: 
  Doubles first- and second-level spells.
  Immunity to first-level spells
  -1 Wisdom
  Weight: 2~
@146  = ~Cap~
@147  = ~The Sage's Boon~
@148  = ~This small, frayed cap sits on the head of the wearer. It looks as if it has seen a great deal of use.~
@149  = ~The Sage's Boon
  This cap has been used by sages for centuries to increases their normal thinking ability. While many learned frown on the use of such items, there is no doubt that this cap has seen much use, and many of its years were spent in the library at Candlekeep.
  Abilities: 
  Intelligence set to 19
  Weight: 1~
@150  = ~An odd book~
@151  = ~How odd.~
@152  = ~Odd, you can't seem to divine what exactly this book is for. It seems to be magical, and likely grants the user some sort of power, but what, you don't know.~
@153  = ~Our Lady of Serenity~
@154  = ~The Lady of Pain the ruler of the planar city of Sigil. Little is known about this powerful being and little is asked.  Those who ask to many questions are either mazed or flayed alive by the ladies blades. The lady is a woman of giant size who is seen floating through the city of Sigil, while her face is serene in appearance her head is surrounded by a ring of magical blades. The lady is as aforementioned a mystery she only exists apparently to protect Sigil and she will expel any god who attempts to enter it.  Her power must indeed be great as she is capable of keeping all the gods in all the planes from entering Sigil and as such you might think she would be worshiped as a god, but any who do worship her a instantly flayed, she rejects all forms of worship. The lady remains a mystery but a mystery that should not be investigated.  ~
@155  = ~You turn and flee in terror, but not before the ghost brushes you with it's bony finger, numbing your body with the chill touch of the grave.~

@157  = ~Earth Elemental Transformation~
@158  = ~Textbook on Item Creation~
@159  = ~This book is a quick and simple guide to the creation of magical items. It is somewhat limited in what items it describes, but it should give a mage plenty to do.
  
Use at your own peril.~
@160  = ~Tutor's Ring~
@161  = ~Tutor's Ring:
  Used by tutors of new Cowled Wizards, these rings grant the tutors protection from some of the less gifted students, some of whose achievements consist of:
- Opening portals to the lower planes
- Causing all cucumbers in the area to spontaneously combust
- Something to do with a lot of brooms (but that was never proven)
  
  STATISTICS:
  +1 Armour Class
  +3 Save vs Spells
  +5% Magic Resistance
  Casts Minor Globe of Invulnerability once/day.~
@162  = ~Red Wizard Orders~
@163  = ~Our contact will meet you in Athkatla. He will be waiting with the Artifact. Once you have it, kill him and return immediately. Avoid the attention of those fool Cowled Wizards at all costs, but if you are intercepted use all force necessary to return with the Artifact. On return, come straight to the Spell Chamber, and we can begin the Unlocking Ritual. On no account must you use spells that open up Planar Portals. They could well trigger the Artifact's defenses. Be warned - fail in this task, and your death shall be slow and painful.
  Signed Zulkir 
  (the note is torn at this point)~
@164  = ~Ring of Free Action:  'Edventar's Gift'
  This ring was given to the reef scavenger and hunter known only as Edventar, by a group of aquatic elves long his friends.  His help in routing the "Pirate Queen" Yenandra of Dambrath was instrumental in their survival, though Yenandra continues to be feared anywhere the water meets land.
  
  STATISTICS:
  
  Special:  The wearer is immune to everything,  magical and otherwise,  that affects mobility in any way.  This includes haste and slow spells.~
@165  = ~Cloak~
@166  = ~Vecna's Spectral Cloak~
@167  = ~The cloak can be made in every possible shape with just about every type of fabric.  The most common forms are a circular piece of fabric with a hole in the center for the head, and fabric draped from neck, connected by a chain, brooch, cord, or pins.  ~
@168  = ~Vecna's Spectral Cloak:
  A garment forged and worn by the Archlich Vecna, a powerful Lich who managed to achieve demi-godhood on one of the outer planes. This cloak easily displays Vecna's powerful magical ability. The cloak is woven from material from the demiplane of shadows. It is totally black, and seems some how alive. The cloak grants the user powerful protections, and is reputed to be able to call shadows to aid the caster.

  STATISTICS:
  25% Magic Resistance
  +50% Cold Resistance
  +1 Armour Class
  +2 Saving Throws
  Immunity to Fear 
  There is a small chance that, when attacked, a shadow will appear to aid the wearer.~
@169  = ~Dusty Rod of Ust Terran~
@170  = ~Dusty Rod of Ust Terran:
  This rod hums with pent magic. Created on the plane of Baator by a powerful lesser demon lord, this wand's power is deadly. The wielder of the rod can point it at his desired target and speak the command word. On doing so, a disintegrating whirl shoots forth, disintegrating the target into a pile of dust.

  STATISTICS:  
  Effect: Thrice/day the rod can be used to instantaneously cast the Disintegrate spell. The target must make a Save vs Spell or be disintegrated
  Range:  120 ft
  Area:  1 creature~
@171  = ~Eye~
@172  = ~Eye Of Vecna~
@173  = ~This eye looks old and rotten. However, when you look at it, you get the distinct impression that it's looking back.~
@174  = ~Eye Of Vecna:
  
  Many tales are told of the Archlich Vecna. 
  It is said that Vecna was one of the Planes' mightiest sorcerers, able to draw life from dust and send it back again, extinguish lives with a glance, and make the earth shudder beneath his touch. He was said to be so powerful that when the end of his life drew near, death refused to take him into its kingdom. 
  And so Vecna died, yet lived on.
  Abandoned by death, Vecna became the master of a vast kingdom on a prime world called Oerth. Neither kind nor just, Lord Vecna's rule was one of great horror and suffering, and it is said his reach was so great that even the Powers of Oerth feared to cross him, for fearing of drawing his eye.
  Yet, while Vecna's gaze traveled ever outward in search of new conquests, he failed to see his own end when it came for him... in the form of his lieutenant, Kas. 
  As was fitting for Vecna's left hand servant, the Archlich had fashioned a terrible weapon for his lieutenant as a symbol of his authority. Vecna made this weapon with such skill it is said that part of the sorcerer entered the blade, and it was this sliver of Vecna that gave the blade its life and its treacherous nature. Where once there was lifeless steel, there became thought, intent, and, perhaps most horrible of all, a voice. 
  The sword whispered treacheries to the ambitious Kas, night upon night, month upon month, year upon year, until one night, the remains of Kas' discipline was seduced by the rippling edge of the blade. Convinced by his blade that he was Vecna's superior, Kas confronted his dread master upon his Dessicated Throne, and the two of them fought a terrible battle. 
  During the battle, Kas was killed, but before he fell, his blade had dismembered his former master, scattering his remains so that no one may draw them together again. And so it has come to pass that pieces of Vecna have made their way across the Planes... one of these is the Eye of Vecna. It carries with it a bloody, violent history, so much so that many scholars refuse to speak of its treacheries, for fear the eye will come to them, seeking to add another victim to its bloody chronology.
  The Eye of Vecna was instrumental in the extermination of the House of Hyeric, once the ruling dynasty in Nyrond. It is said to have been behind the sundering of the Conclave of Tyssis-on-the-Sea, which led to the three-cycle war that poisoned the seas of Malhatai and left the oceanic world barren of life. On the ashen Plane of Ghalentir, it possessed the gentle father of Sasaran, a babe with the potential to lead his suffering people from their shadowed lands to the Gates of Paradise... had not the eye drove Sasaran's father to murder his son as he lay sleeping in his crib. All these kingdoms, all these futures, the Eye of Vecna laid waste.
  The Eye's powers are said to shift with each new owner, but one thing is certain: no good ever comes from whoever has the misfortune to possess it. It is destined to betray its wearer at a critical moment, failing him when he needs its power the most. 
  Effects:
  You can gouge out your normal eye and replace it with the eye of vecna (ouch). The effects will be permanent, and can never be reversed unless a replacement eye is found.
   
  Doubles all 1st Level Mage Spells
  Doubles all 2nd Level Mage Spells
  +10% Resistance to Magic
  +2 Save vs. Death 
  +2 Save Versus spell
  Immunity to Power Word Kill.
  -2 to Charisma
  -2 to Base hit points
  Weight: 0~
