  +5% Magic Resistance
  Immunity to 1st- and 2nd-level spells
  Immunity to Finger of Death and Power Word - Kill spells~
@193  = ~Balduran's Ring~
@194  = ~This ring seems very old, yet it obviously holds some sort of power.~
@195  = ~Balduran's Ring:
  The legendary explorer and adventurer Balduran, who founded the city of Baldur's Gate, wore this ring until his final voyage, when he left it in the possession of his next of kin. The ring, like most of Balduran's equipment, is heavily enchanted to protect the user. It is unknown why Balduran did not take the ring with him on his last trip (to, as you know, the Werewolf Island). It is believed, however, that Balduran wore so much magical equipment that the latent magic had some strange side effects.
  
  EFFECTS:
  +1 Constitution
  +1 Saving Throws
  +10% Fire and Cold Resistances 
  Immunity to Fireball and Lightning Bolt spells~
